<text>Vought was an American aircraft company founded by Chance M. Vought.

Vought may also refer to:

* Chance M. Vought (1890–1930), American aviation pioneer, engineer, and founder of the Vought company
* Russell Vought (born 1976), American political organizer and government official
* Vought American (Vought International in the television series), an antagonist corporation in the fictional universe of &quot;The Boys&quot;</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q644459" start="0" end="6" title="Vought" label="Vought"/>
